Submit bass tabs

Got some bass tabs that you want to share with the world? Send them to us!

Rules of submission

  • By submitting you agree that this tab is your own work or that you have the permission of the original author of the tab to post it here.
  • Publication on the website depends on the decision of the staff. We will do our best to approve tabs as quickly as possible. If your tab is not up to standards you will be notified and we will help you correct it so that it is fit for approval.
  • Once you submit a tab you permit the bigbasstabs.com website to publish it indefinitely (and make any necessary edits). You will be credited as the author of the tab for as long as the tab is published.

Listen on Sonos

You can listen to Chris Country on your Sonos system, just by finding us in the RadioPlayer listings.

The best way to listen is by firstly, choosing RadioPlayer in the list of music services that are available...

Then, on the list of stations, you'll see Chris Country!

Double-click on our name and we'll start playing. You can then also save us as a favourite station, and listen to us any time on your Sonos device!

Technical Information


CCCT is an 197-seat theatre that provides unique opportunities for directors and designers to tell stories from the intimate to the spectacular.

Before embarking on a project it is important to know what the space can and cannot accommodate; please refer to the technical information below or contact Production Manager Mike Reynolds at with any questions.

In-Person Auditions

Performer - In-Person Auditions

In-person auditions for the 2017 Season will be held on April 2 and April 9, 2017 from 9am to 5pm at Rhythms Performing Arts Center, 1114 1st St, Novato, CA 94945  You only need to attend one day of auditions.  

To sign-up for an In-Person Audition, just click this link and submit the form!

For information about recorded auditions, click here.


In-Person Audition Requirements

Show Requirement
 All  Resume of any previous theater or performing experience.  Submitted via email no later than one week before audition.
 All  Dance audition.
 All  One one-minute song (not from a show MST is producing this year)  
 All One one-minute monologue (not from a show MST is producing this year)  
 All     Principal audition side (if any)


If you have a photo or headshot, please attach it to your resume (as page two). This is not requried, but it helps us remember you. It does not need to be a professional photo. A well-lit recent candid of you smiling and happy from your shoulders to the top of your head will be great. Don't try to be a model or artsy. We just want to remember you.


Audition Day Schedule 


Time Audition Section
 9:00am – 10:30am      Dance auditions
 10:30am – 3:00pm  General singing and acting auditions  
 3:00pm – 5:00pm  Principal Call-Backs 


Dance Auditions

You must attend dance auditions at 9am. The routine will be uploaded to this website in early March.  The routine will also be taught on audition day.


General Singing and Acting Auditions

General singing and acting auditions for all shows begin at 10:30.  You will be notified approximately two days before auditions of your approximate general audition time.  You will be allowed  a one-minute song and a one-minute monlogue. You should plan on staying until at least 3pm if you are interested in an ensemble part and until 5pm if you are interested in a principal part. At 3pm, auditionees not needed for call-backs will be released. 

Photos and Measurements - During the General Singing and Acting audition period, we will also take your photo and our costumers will take your measurements.


Principal Call-backs

After you have done your general audition, you may asked to stay for call backs. Principal call-backs are from 3pm to 5pm on each day of auditions.  You will be told by 3pm if you are needed for call backs and which Principal Audition Sides we would like to see you perform.  Principal sides will be posted to the MST web site by mid-February so you can prepare. If you have submitted an application, you will be notified via email when they are available.

Principal audition sides are short scenes, speeches or parts of songs that give us a better idea of well you fit a leading or featured role. If you are interested in a lead or featured role in any of the the shows, you should download the sides for those roles and practice performing the side.  Do not perform these sides as part of your general audition. These sides are for callbacks only. 

To sign-up for an In-Person Audition, just click this link and submit the form!

Ticket information

Tickets for our 2014 event are on sale. Buy your tickets now!

You can either pick and chose the shows you want to go to, or you can buy a pass for the whole weekend, which allows entry to all shows.

Prices on the door will be higher, so buy in advance to save! You will need to bring a print out of your e-ticket or your paper ticket to the wristband exchange point. Details of the wristband exchange point will be published soon.

Terms and conditions apply, which you agree to upon purchasing a ticket:

  • The Frog and Fiddle is a strictly 18+ venue
  • You agree comply with the rules of the individual venues. Each venue reserves the right to refuse admission and to search customers upon entry if required. Please carry a driving license or passport as proof of age
  • You consent to yourself being captured in photographs and videos at the festival, which may be used by Tribe Festivals Ltd and our partners
  • Some venues are 18+. Please check before buying and get in touch if you aren't sure. Tickets incorrectly bought by or for under 18s will not be refunded
  • Tickets are non refundable, except in the highly unlikely case of the festival being canceled or postponed. Refunds are not available for customers who have been either refused entry or ejected from venues due to breaches of the venue rules. We can not re-issue lost or stolen tickets.
  • The line-up may be subject to change. We will keep you informed of any changes via the website. Refunds are not available for changes to the line-up.
